description: Provides a list of Medical Scribe jobs that match the specified criteria. If no criteria are specified, all Medical Scribe jobs are returned. To get detailed information about a specific Medical Scribe job, use the operation.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: Lists all Medical Scribe jobs that have the status specified in your request. Jobs are ordered by creation date, with the newest job first.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: If NextToken is present in your response, it indicates that not all results are displayed. To view the next set of results, copy the string associated with the NextToken parameter in your results output, then run your request again including NextToken with the value of the copied string. Repeat as needed to view all your results.

nested_items.name: MedicalScribeJobSummaries
nested_items.description: Provides a summary of information about each result.

nested_items.name: MedicalScribeJobName
nested_items.description: The name of the Medical Scribe job. Job names are case sensitive and must be unique within an Amazon Web Services account.

nested_items.name: CreationTime
nested_items.description: The date and time the specified Medical Scribe job request was made.

nested_items.name: StartTime
nested_items.description: The date and time your Medical Scribe job began processing.

nested_items.name: CompletionTime
nested_items.description: The date and time the specified Medical Scribe job finished processing.

nested_items.name: LanguageCode
nested_items.description: The language code used to create your Medical Scribe job. US English ( en-US) is the only supported language for Medical Scribe jobs.

nested_items.name: MedicalScribeJobStatus
nested_items.description: Provides the status of the specified Medical Scribe job.

nested_items.name: FailureReason
nested_items.description: If MedicalScribeJobStatus is FAILED, FailureReason contains information about why the transcription job failed. See also: Common Errors.
